        content:
          'Giant Steps is the fifth studio album by jazz musician John Coltrane as leader. It was released in February 1960 on Atlantic Records. This was his first album as leader for Atlantic Records, with which he had signed a new contract the previous year. The record is regarded as one of the most influential jazz albums of all time. Many of its tracks have become practice templates for jazz saxophonists. In 2004, it was one of fifty recordings chosen that year by the Library of Congress to be added to the National Recording Registry. It attained gold record status in 2018, having sold 500,000 copies.\n\nTwo tracks, "Naima" and "Syeeda\'s Song Flute", are respectively named after Coltrane\'s wife at the time and her daughter, whom he adopted. A third, "Mr. P.C.", takes its name from the initials of bassist Paul Chambers, who played on the album. A fourth, "Cousin Mary", is named in honor of Mary Lyerly, Coltrane\'s younger cousin.\n\nPersonnel:\nJohn Coltrane â tenor saxophone\nTommy Flanagan â piano\nWynton Kelly â piano on "Naima"\nPaul Chambers â bass\nArt Taylor â drums\nJimmy Cobb â drums on "Naima"\nCedar Walton â piano on "Giant Steps" and âNaima" alternate versions\nLex Humphries â drums on "Giant Steps" and âNaima" alternate versions\n\nProduction:\nNesuhi ErtegÃ¼n â producer\nTom Dowd, Phil Iehle â engineer\nLee Friedlander â photography\nMarvin Israel â cover design\nNat Hentoff â liner notes\nBob Carlton, Patrick Milligan â reissue supervision\nBill Inglot, Dan Hersch â digital remastering\nRachel Gutek â reissue design\nHugh Brown â reissue art direction\nVanessa Atkins, Steven Chean, Julee Stover â reissue editorial supervision\nTed Meyers, Elizabeth Pavone â reissue editorial coordination\n\nRelease history\n1960 â Atlantic Records SD 1311, vinyl record\n1987 â Atlantic Records, first generation compact disc\n1994 â Mobile Fidelity Gold CD - MFSL \n1998 â Rhino Records R2 75203, Deluxe Edition compact disc and 180-gram vinyl record\n2020 â Atlantic Records R2 625106/603497848393, 60 Years Deluxe Edition, 2 CDs (Remastered Album + Outtakes) <a href="https://www.last.fm/music/John+Coltrane/Giant+Steps">Read more on Last.fm</a>. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.',
