        content:
          'Nectar is the second studio album by Joji, following his successful debut record, BALLADS 1, released in October of 2018.\n\nAfter initially announcing a July 2020 release date, Joji postponed the album to September 25, 2020 in response to the COVID-19 pandemic and the Black Lives Matter protests.\n\nThe album boasts a variety of featured singers, rappers, and producers, including: Diplo, Omar Apollo, Lil Yachty, rei brown, BENEE, and Yves Tumor.\n\nThe first single from the record, âSanctuary,â was released on June 14, 2019. The recordâs second single, âRun,â released on February 7, 2020. The third single (The more streamed and popular one amongst the four), âGimme Love,â was released on April 16, 2020, along with the announcement of the title of the album and that it was originally intended to be released on July 10, 2020. The fourth single, a collaboration with Diplo called âDaylight,â was released on August 6, 2020.\n\nThe album takes a sonically different approach from "BALLADS 1", with a sound thatâs less focused on Jojiâs typical melancholy, lo-fi sound. Instead, the album takes a mix of many retroelements instrumentation from older Joji projects that never got to see the light of streaming services. <a href="https://www.last.fm/music/Joji/Nectar">Read more on Last.fm</a>. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.',
